  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "Currently to wait for a contract deployment in hardhat-ethers you do something like this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst contract = Contract.deploy();\r\nawait contract.deployed();\r\n```\r\n\r\nUnderneath I imagine this `deployed` function calls `wait` which accepts an argument of number of confirmations. It would be nice if we could pass nConfirmations into `deployed` to be passed into `wait` to end up with something like:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst contract = Contract.deploy();\r\n// wait for 4 confirmations\r\nawait contract.deployed(4);\r\n```\r\n",
